name: the first five ingredients can tell you a lot about the quality of a product as they make up the bulk of the product. Ideally
you're looking for quality protein sources with a minimum of cheap starches
fillers or by-products. Continuing down the ingredient list
look for ingredients that resemble real food with a minimal number of unpronounceable chemicals - the same as you would for human food.
